Name: Baku
Description: Baku is the capital of Azerbaijan.

Name: Ganja
Description: Ganja (Azeri: Gəncə) is a city in the Ganja Region of northwestern Azerbaijan.

Name: Lankaran
Description: Lankaran, Lenkeran, or Lenkoran is in Azerbaijan's Talysh Region.

Name: Nakhchivan
Description: There is more than one place called Nakhchivan:

Name: Qabala
Description: Qabala is a city in Azerbaijan's Qabala Region.

Name: Sheki
Description: Sheki (Şəki; also Seki or Shaki) is Azerbaijan's true travel gem, a small city off on the forested slopes of the Greater Caucasus Mountains. Rich in Islamic architecture, Silk Road history, good food, and friendly people, this is travel and leisure in the Caucasus at its finest.

Name: Shemakha
Description: Shamakhi (Shemakha, Şamaxı) is a town in Azerbaijan's Baku Region, capital of the Shamakhi Rayon.

Name: Qobustan
Description: Qobustan is a city in Azerbaijan's Baku Region.

Name: Göygöl National Park
Description: Göygöl National Park is in Ganja Region of Azerbaijan.

Name: Khinalug
Description: Khinalug the highest (2250 m above sea level), most remote and isolated village in Northeastern Azerbaijan and among the highest in the Caucasus.

Name: Nabran
Description: Nabran is a city in the Northeastern region of Azerbaijan, 45 km north of Khachmaz, close to the Russian border.

Name: Quba
Description: Quba (or Guba) is a city in Northeastern Azerbaijan, on the northern slope of the Caucasus, 180 km northwest of Baku.

Name: Lahich
Description: Lahich (Lahıc, Lahij) is a mountain village in the Sheki Region.

Name: Qax
Description: Qax, Qakh, also Kakhi (Georgian კახი) or sometimes Gakh is a town in Azerbaijan's Sheki Region.
